column1: 10857=MSc in Smart Cities and Communities=Master=The EMJM SMACCs is a unique 2-year 120 ECTS Master Degree
column2: aiming at educating the next generation of engineers and scientists in Smart Cities and Communities.The SMACCs implements a curriculum specialized on fundamental pillars of a city sustainability
column3: i.e. Energy
column5: Buildings
column6: Urban Planning and ICT as a key enabling factor for implementing sustainable solutions. Professionals mastering these aspects are urgently needed to accompany the sustainable and smart transition of our cities
column7: through the massive deployment of multi-sector renewable energy communities in urban and peri-urban areas.The SMACCs proposes an international curriculum jointly designed and delivered by 4 European HEIs (Belgium
column8: Spain
column9: Greece
column10: Finland) based on compulsory physical mobility between the four HEIs
column11: with the support of more than 50 public or private Associated Partners from Europe and the whole world
column12: in order to boost the students’ exposure to the professional and academic sectors.The programme fosters excellence through the high quality of its academic contents
column13: developed in connection with the research activities of the 4 SMACCs HEIs and the ecosystem of partners
column14: and through the attraction of the best students worldwide thanks to the implementation of a competitive
column15: fair and transparent application system.The EMJM will benefit the following target groups:*Students & Young professionals: acquiring new state-of-the-art knowledge will improve chances on the labour market
column16: in which demand in energy
column17: ICT
column18: transport and buildings is continuously growing*Academic staff: the MSc will increase the opportunities for research collaboration and exchange of good practices*Universities: the programme will foster international cooperation and visibility and diversify the recruitment of students*Companies: the MSc will provide a source of knowledgeable workers
column19: at regional and transnational levels*Society: will benefit from the latest innovation in Smart Cities and Communities=https://erasmus-plus.ec.europa.eu/projects/search/details/101128215=2=15/09/2024-15/12/2024=Sep-25=6.0=B2=None=True

column1: 10858=European Master For Industry in Microwave Electronics and Photonics=Master=EMIMEP is an integrated learning programme centred on microwave engineering and photonic technologies preparing a new generation of engineers for the next decade of sustainable technological solutions. EMIMEP is based on excellence and it is a concrete solution to the increasing demand for highly qualified talents to foster academic and industrial innovation. Areas covered range from the fundamentals of microwave electronics and photonics to their implementations with new technologies
column2: combining analogue electronics
column3: lasers
column5: nano-photonics
column6: energy harvesting and antennas.The partners are: University of Limoges (FR)
column7: University of Brescia (IT)
column8: University of the Basque Country (SP) and Friedrich-Schiller University of Jena (DE). EMIMEP also includes 5 academic associated partners. A panel of 49 Associated Partners
column9: including companies
column10: research laboratories and associations
column11: will support the EMIMEP programme and will constitute an effective network for Master’s theses and future career development.The first 3 semesters are based on lectures and lab sessions
column12: while the last one is based on independent work related to the Master thesis. The first-year programme combines a first placement period in France and then in Italy with a Research and Industrial Week in Romania. Students in the second year will enhance their learning around one of the four paths available at the 3rd semester: towards greener power management in electronics and photonics in Limoges
column13: Technologies for High-Frequency applications in Bilbao
column14: Communication Technologies in Brescia
column15: Optics Photonics and Quantum Technologies in Jena. After a Summer School in Catania (IT) and an active participation to the European MicroWave Week Conference
column16: at the end of the master
column17: the students are awarded a joint diploma. EMIMEP graduated students can be recruited directly by companies or pursue a PhD programme in universities
column18: research institutes or industrial doctorates.=https://erasmus-plus.ec.europa.eu/projects/search/details/101128187=2=21/10/2024-21/12/2024=Oct-25=7.0=B2=None=True

column1: 10859=Safe and Reliable Nuclear Applications=Master=SARENA
column2: which stands for SAfe and REliable Nuclear Applications
column3: is an Erasmus+ supported EMJMD programme aiming to develop scientific
column4: technical and management skills enabling engineers to work internationally in all domains related to nuclear energy and applications.The SARENA programme consists of a two-year Master of Science in Nuclear Engineering
column5: fully taught in English
column6: which provides a dual approach of academic teaching and practical experience in the field of nuclear applications within the framework of an international mobility context. The teaching programme focuses on the acquisition of global knowledge and skills in nuclear physics and chemistry
column7: nuclear engineering
column8: radioactive waste management
column9: decommissioning
column10: as well as reactor operation and safety. The content has also been updated to cover recent trends in the nuclear industry
column11: notably socio-economic perspectives in energy transition and the topic of Small Modular Reactors (SMR). The teaching programme is strongly supported by practical experience
column12: notably hands-on training in facilities available in the consortium institutions
column13: used to develop high quality R&D activities
column14: as well as workshops and trainings within laboratories and industrial facilities provided by Associate Partners (industrial companies
column15: regulators and international organizations). To be completed
column16: the programme requires conducting a mandatory internship in a laboratory or an industrial company
column17: thereby optimizing insertion in the labour market.In tune with the actual needs of both the labour market and European challenges with regards to maintaining a stable decarbonized energy mix
column18: the SARENA programme aims to educate international nuclear engineers with a strong European culture
column19: aware of the energy
column20: environmental
column21: and climate context
column22: yet ready to face contemporary challenges in the industry. Our proposed master programme thus aims to become an international standard for teaching nuclear engineering and applications.=https://erasmus-plus.ec.europa.eu/projects/search/details/101128167=2=01/10/2024-01/12/2024=Sep-25=6.0=C1=None=True

column1: 10860=Education Policies for Global Development=Master=Education Policies for Global Development (GLOBED) is a two-year European master’s degree that specialises in the complex relationship between education policy and international development. It aims to provide students with up to date knowledge to address the main challenges that education systems face
column2: and to identify the most suitable policies through which education can contribute to human
column3: social and economic development. Seven successful editions offer significant evidence that GLOBED has become a highly distinguished international Master's degree in the field of global studies
column5: with an exponentially increasing demand from low- and middle-income countries. Developed by four HEIs (UAB
column7: UB
column8: and UCY)
column9: and supported by almost 50 associate partners (including international organisations
column10: aid agencies and INGOs)
column11: the next GLOBED cycle includes important innovations: 1) partnerships: new special associate partners will offer course electives to enable students’ research to be appropriately tailored to their regional context=https://erasmus-plus.ec.europa.eu/projects/search/details/101128259=2=15/11/2024-15/02/2025=Sep-25=7.0=B2=None=True

column1: 10861=Communications Engineering and Data Science=Master=Although the trend is already clear in current communication networks
column2: future developments such as 6G will necessarily rely its operation on data collection
column3: analysis and actions
column4: in order to adapt to the changing conditions of the environment. Knowledge of Artificial Intelligence and Data Science is becoming a need for network engineering
column5: computer science and telecommunications graduates
column6: and although some programs are starting to introduce these concepts in the curriculum
column7: few programs tackle both areas in an integrated way. Hence
column8: this proposal of a M.Sc. degree in Communications Engineering and Data Science is timely
column9: and capable of attracting students not only from Europe but also from broader international regions
column10: namely from Asia
column11: Africa
column12: and Latin America.We propose an EMJM programme backed by five well-known technical European Universities that tackles the aforementioned need of an integrated Communications and Data Science (CoDaS) approach. The proposal builds on the experience of three of the partners in the current CoDaS scheme of double-degree agreements
column13: and we plan to expand it with two more partners
column14: the collaboration of industrial partners and research centres
column15: and boost it with the Erasmus Mundus seal
column16: and an increased level of cooperation (summer schools
column17: exchange of teaching staff
column18: workshops to name a couple of examples).In the four editions of the program
column19: we expect to attract a total of up to 159 students (of which 56 are from European countries) with a technical readiness which will allow them to quickly integrate in a company or pursue a research career. Such workforce will definitely improve the competitiveness of European industry. We also firmly believe that after these four editions the degree will have reached a level of maturity and prestige that will allow it to self-sustain and become the first truly European-wide master’s program in Communications and Data Science.=https://erasmus-plus.ec.europa.eu/projects/search/details/101128281=2=10/09/2024-15/12/2024=Sep-25=6.0=B2=None=True

column1: 10862=Erasmus Mundus Masters Program in Public Policy=Master=Mundus MAPP is a 2 year transnational joint master’s degree accredited under the EA. It is offered by an international consortium composed of academic and professional partners. CEU PU (Austria)
column2: the ISS (the Netherlands)
column3: the UoY (UK) and IBEI (Spain) deliver the teaching (UAB
column4: UPF and UB are the degree awarding institutions for IBEI). They are joined by 10 professional partners with global outreach
column5: which provide professional experience opportunities and help assess and raise awareness of the programme. column1: 10922=MSc European Forestry=Master=The Master of Science in European Forestry (MSc EF) is a two-year Master programme that provides academic education in the field of sustainable resource management with special emphasis on recent opportunities and challenges in bio-economy. In MSc EF

column6: Austria and Transilvania University of Brasov
column7: Romania. In addition

The objective of MSc EF is to educate experts who have a through understanding of sustainable forest bioeconomy as well as of European business culture. The Curriculum of the programme is specifically designed to take into consideration the needs of potential employers. The programme's language of instruction is English with great opportunities to learn local cultures and languages in six different European countries. The first academic year includes two study Modules that have been jointly designed by the MSc EF Consortium. Module 1 (12 ECTS) improves students' professional knowledge and Module 2 (18 ECTS) gives students practical perspective (1-month long field course) and familiarises students with the working life (2-month long internship). The package of elective courses (30 ECTS) gives students a possibility to deepen their knowledge and skills on their desired topics. The second academic year is based on Study Module 3 (60 ECTS) where each second-year host university offers a package of specialised courses (30 ECTS) through jointly agreed study tracks according to his own field of expertise. Master�s Thesis (30 ECTS) and Online Thesis Seminar are also included in Study Module 3. The European Forestry Forum including job fairs and graduating ceremony comes after this Module and brings all the students and graduates together again at the end of the second academic year. All students graduate with the ability to work in multicultural environments and with the latest knowledge on forest management and bioeconomy and policy-making in Europe. The MSc EF graduates receive a joint degree or a double degree i.e. two MSc degree certificates depending on their chosen second year host university. In the double degree option
column10: the first one is always issued by the coordinating university (University of Eastern Finland)
column11: because it is the host institution for the first academic year. The other degree certificate is issued by that second-year host university where the student carries out his/her second academic year.=https://ec.europa.eu/programmes/erasmus-plus/projects/eplus-project-details/#project/610532-EPP-1-2019-1-FI-EPPKA1-JMD-MOB=2=14/11/2024-14/03/2025=Sep-25=6.0=C1=None=True

column1: 10928=Euroculture: Society
column2: Politics and Culture in a Global Context=Master=The 120 ECTS European master ‘Euroculture: Society

column1: 10956=4CITIES+ Erasmus Mundus Joint Master Degree in Urban Studies=Master=4CITIES+ is a two-year
column2: 120 ECTS Master in Urban Studies
column3: jointly organised by six universities in four cities: Brussels (Vrije Universiteit Brussel
column5: Vienna (Universität Wien)
column6: Copenhagen (Københavns Universitet) and Madrid (Universidad Autónoma de Madrid
column7: Universidad Complutense de Madrid). The main objective of 4CITIES+ is to acquire a comprehensive and comparative knowledge of European cities within different welfare state systems in a globalising world
column8: underpinned by the interdisciplinarity and mix of analysis and action that is characteristic of the field of urban studies. The multifaceted complexity of cities is difficult to grasp
column9: and so 4CITIES+ takes a holistic and immersive approach. Theory and practice are seen as mirrors
column10: each critically reflecting the other. The city is engaged as an evolving narrative
column11: more dialogic than linear
column12: and students learn to see “The City”
column13: to hear it
column14: to participate in it
column15: and to understand it
column16: all while experimenting with their role in shaping it.4CITIES+ offers three study tracks. The Classical Track: this is the track for students that want to get a broad
column17: interdisciplinary urban studies education in four fascinating
column18: historical and complex capital cities of Europe. Additional excursions to a diverse set of cities such as Rotterdam
column19: Antwerp
column20: Zagreb
column21: Belgrade
column22: Malmö
column23: and Zaragoza are also organised in each semester. For students following this track
column24: the programme begins in Brussels in mid-September and remains there until the end of January. After a break in February
column25: the Vienna semester runs from March through June. The third semester
column26: in Copenhagen
column27: starts in September and ends mid-December. The final semester
column29: begins in early February and wraps up at the end of May. Throughout the two years
column30: students work on their master thesis
column31: which is due on the first of September. Thesis defences and the graduation ceremony take place in Brussels in late September. The Research Track: a track for students that want to pursue a PhD and/or research career after their Master degree
column32: this track allows for more specialisation within one of the subdomains of urban studies. Students also start in Brussels and continue in Vienna
column33: but in the second year can follow elective courses as well as a research internship with one of our more than twenty associated academic partners across Europe. The Practice Track: this is the track for students that want to gain relevant work experience during their Masters education. Students study in Brussels and Vienna in the first year
column34: but in the second year can follow elective courses and do a work placement with one of our associated professional partners anywhere in Europe. 4CITIES+ graduates will receive either a joint degree (Classical Track) or a multiple degree (Research and Practice Tracks).=https://ec.europa.eu/programmes/erasmus-plus/projects/eplus-project-details/#project/599110-EPP-1-2018-1-BE-EPPKA1-JMD-MOB=2=12/09/2024-12/12/2024=Sep-25=7.0=B2=None=True
